ide context for this cornerstone of Judeo-Tunisian letters.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aJewsxFictionxTunisia. 0aJewszTunisiavFiction. 4aAlliance israélite universelle. 4aFrench colonialism. 4aJewish history. 4aNorth Africa. 4aTunisian literature. 4aminority literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBrozgal, Lia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKuntz, Jane1 aStein, Sarah Abrevaya, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360229840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503602298423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503602298.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles